ANALYSIS
Thisbill:
I. Requires that animal care centers notify dogowners when adog will beleft unattended and if
thecenterisnotequippedwithafunctioningfireprotectionsprinklersystem.
II. Requires that animal care centers report injuries that occur to people or animals on the
animalcarecenter'sproperty.
III. Enables local law enforcement to annually inspect animal care centers and provides a
penaltyfornotmaintainingpropercareoftheanimalcarecenter.
